#META# contentSummary: A memo sent by ʿAlī b. Najīb and Muḥammad b. Najīb to two *shiḥna *officers, informing them that a commander called Ḥādhiq has been dispatched as backup to help them recover the full tax payment of 90 donkey loads of grain and hay owed by peasants in the Zīrdamān Valley to the commander Sayf al-Dīn Najm al-Umarāʾ Qutluq Arslān Tegin (?) after the peasants expressed resistance and insisted that they would pay only 70 donkey loads.
